// https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/ἄλλως https://logeion.uchicago.edu/ἄλλως
// otherwise
// ---Cunliffe---
// ἄλλως [ἄλλος].
// 1. Otherwise, differently, so as to bring about a
//    different result --In other circumstances
//    --Reversing a previous decision: μετεβούλευσαν
// 2. In some other form: εἰ ἀ. δοίης δωτίνην --For
//    some other reason --In novel fashion: ἑψιάασθαι
// 3. καὶ ἀ., as it is, at the best of times, without
//    that: ἀγήνωρ ἐστὶ καὶ ἀ.
// 4. Otherwise (connoting improvement): πάρος οὐκ ἔσσεται
//    ἀ. --In other and better wise, better, more
//    effectually: σαωσέμεν  οὔ κεν ἀ. θεὸς
//    τεύξειεν
// 5. Otherwise than with due regard to truth, idly, at
//    random: ἀ. ψεύδονται
// 6.  With other result than that hoped for, in vain,
//    fruitlessly: ἀ. ἠρήσατο

{
  "word":"ἄλλως",
  "medium":"otherwise"
}
      